remarks:        *********** Supported BGP Communities ******************
remarks:        ---------------------------------------------------------
remarks:        0:<peer-as> - Deny announcing a route to the
remarks:        peer with <peer-as>.
remarks:        
remarks:        59613:<peer-as> - Permit announcing a route to
remarks:        the peer with <peer-as>.
remarks:        Permit community has more "weight" rather than deny
remarks:        community so if you announce a prefix with both permit
remarks:        and deny communities the announce will be PERMITTED.
remarks:        
remarks:        0:59613 - Deny announcing a prefix to anybody.
remarks:        Useful with permit communities if you want to announce
remarks:        a prefix only to the selected autonomous systems.
remarks:        
remarks:        65001:<peer-as> - Prepend your ASN 1 time while
remarks:        announcing to <peer-as>
remarks:        
remarks:        65002:<peer-as> - Prepend your ASN 2 times while
remarks:        announcing to <peer-as>
remarks:        
remarks:        65003:<peer-as> - Prepend your ASN 3 times while
remarks:        announcing to <peer-as>
remarks:        
remarks:        59613:59613 (or none) - Announce prefix to anybody
remarks:        (default behavior).
remarks:        
remarks:        59613:666 - blackhole trafic to the announced prefix.
remarks:        We accept prefixes upto /32 length if they have the
remarks:        blackhole community set, but only those prefixes which
remarks:        are in your as-set object.
remarks:        Please ensure your router accepts any prefix marked by
remarks:        59613:666 community (you can drop traffic to those
remarks:        prefixes on your side as well).
remarks:        
remarks:        59613:100 - Deny our GGC nodes to serve traffic to
remarks:        the announced prefix.
